$interpreted: Tindoiimu: (Should I... go after Toyokuni? ...And what on earth's happening out there...)
Tindoiimu: (This is a catastrophe...)
Sophie: Look out, Tindoiimu!
Sophie: Behind you! It's behind you!
Tindoiimu: (It's... the Udumbara seal...!)
Sophie: Quick, Tindoiimu, hide yourself!
Eidatyr: Too late! She's done for!
Tindoiimu: (...Such intense light... I've... seen this before!)
Sophie: Ah, it's that guy who helped us back in the Desert Kingdom!
Uzziah: Still not strong enough...
Tindoiimu: (Did he just... beat back the Monster of Judgment? And that strength of his... really reminds me of Juan-Yun...)
Uzziah: It looks as if the monsters in the East have absorbed a lot of Soul Energy...
Uzziah: You ought to... flee to the south. The coming battles will take place in the north. I'd better go, too.
Eidatyr: The north!? You mean among the Clan? Hey, answer me!
Ru-yi: The monsters are all g-g-gone... Are we safe now?
Sophie: Uhh... guess so...
Tachilaanda: ...You guess so? Guess again.
Eidatyr: Ugh, here we go again...
Tindoiimu: ...What do you mean by that, Tachilaanda?
Tachilaanda: Hee... Don't play dumb, Sis. You'll only be hurting me and my Insect brethren even more.
Insect Guard: I saw... I saw Her Majesty...
Tachilaanda: Have no fear, General Jihasaha and I will protect you. Go on, tell everyone what you just saw in the cell.
Insect Guard: Yes, Your Highness... When the Princess was taking food to that Komainu, the two of them mentioned trapping the monsters and perishing together,
Insect Guard: and then the monsters came charging in and the cell was destroyed... When I came to, the Komainu and the Princess had both disappeared...
Tachilaanda: Tsk... You helped our enemy to escape, Sis. You've joined with them and plotted against us, how could you!?
Tindoiimu: Tachilaanda! Don't hurl such lies at me! Toyokuni escaped all by himself. I wanted to go after him—
Tachilaanda: Yaaagh! Save me, Jihasaha!
Tindoiimu: Jihasaha, don't tell me even you think of me as a traitor—
Jihasaha: ...The Komainu certainly didn't have you all locked up when I found you.
Tindoiimu: That's because...
Jihasaha: You may have gone to the Alliance on behalf of the Insects... but you stayed there too long. That Komainu had real affection for you. And you?
Jihasaha: Even if you weren't the one who let him go, would you really have gone after him? Knowing that he'd face certain death?
Tindoiimu: ...
Tindoiimu: (...It's true... I did hesitate...)
Tachilaanda: ...Sis, do you finally admit... that you've never been on our side, not for a long time now...
Agitated Insect Soldier: Princess! Why would you betray us!
Indignant Insect Soldier: Traitor! You've betrayed us all!
Tindoiimu: No... You're mixing things up! The Insects... have always been my...
Indignant Insect Soldier: You'd dare plot against our Queen? Everyone, take her away!
Eidatyr: ...Ahahaha, goddamn it. Wherever we go, it's always the same old show. I'm sick of this!
Hanbei: What are you standing around for? Run for it!
Sophie: Yeah! Even if you stay behind, they'll never listen to you now! They don't believe you, but we do!
Tindoiimu: (...Should I... flee the Insects...?)
Tachilaanda: Sis, even with things as bad as they are already, you're still helping outsiders to harm us?
Tindoiimu: (I'm condemned in the East... and now, am I to be condemned among the Insects, too?)
Eidatyr: If you've got a deathwish, Princess, please leave us out of it. Can't you see you've got this chain of fools here ready to bust our asses for you?
Tindoiimu: ......
Eidatyr: I know what you're thinking.
Eidatyr: This gang of idiots are the reason you've been shedding all this blood, sweat and tears. If they don't want you anymore, why the hell should you go on fighting any longer?
Tindoiimu: ...How did you... Have you... seen this all before?
Eidatyr: People are all the same, wherever you go. But you've got to keep on going, keep pushing ahead.
Tindoiimu: ...But how can I... I don't even know where to go...
Eidatyr: High and mighty as you are, Princess, you must have had people putting their lives on the line for you before.
Tindoiimu: ...I...
Eidatyr: If so, you ought to keep going.
Eidatyr: You're not welcome in the East or the Insect Tribe, so what's left to think about? Just be a good little sidekick and come to the north with us!
Tachilaanda: Ugh, you're ignoring me again! Sis!
Tachilaanda: Get the lot of them! Whichever brave warrior catches the Princess shall be handsomely rewarded!!
Tindoiimu: ......
Eidatyr: Good choice!
Eidatyr: Now let's get the hell out of here!
Tindoiimu: ...Jihasaha...
Jihasaha: You have to give it all you've got. Else I'll have broken my oath for nothing.
Tachilaanda: ...Have they escaped?
Jihasaha: It was my own incompetence, I was unable to stop them.
Tachilaanda: Don't blame yourself, General. I'd prefer not to see my family's blood spilled here, anyway.
Tachilaanda: Maybe... this is for the best. Don'tcha think?
Jihasaha: ...Yes, my Queen.
